                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/9–2650: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-09-26T13:29:00-05:00"
                            >September 26, 1950—1:29 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 36. Jebb told Gross September 25 p. m.,
                    Vishinsky had failed to respond to Jebb’s request for interview to discuss
                    appointment <pb facs="0142" n="126" xml:id="pg_126"/> of <gloss target="#t_SYG1"
                        >SYG</gloss>. With annoyance, Jebb said he thought the only course now
                    remaining was to put matter directly in <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>. Gross
                    replied this course seemed premature at the moment and he would like to discuss
                    matter with Jebb again in next few days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
